HR DirectSupport all the selected countries across Asia Pacific by serving as employees' first point-of-contact for questions about HR policies and processes. Responsible for answering employees' queries on a timely and professional manner, routing them to the appropriate individual and function as necessary while tracking all customer contacts in the internal corporate database in accordance to global process & policy.This role (based in Singapore) will be a member of the Asia Pacific HR Shared Services team reporting to the HR Service Manager, Asia Pacific. Serves as a first point of contact for current and former employees' questions on HR policies and/or processes.Receives customer requests and where appropriate, redirects to the relevant internal and external parties for resolution.Reviews and selects product and sub product types in Case Management system and documents down requests.Provides self-service support through guiding employees step by step on their SAP transactions or responding to other information requests or concerns; generates requests' trend for management's review and actions.Ensures that customers' questions are fully addressed and escalating complex/difficult questions to 2nd Tier (per Tier 2 Assignment Guidelines).Completes customer request and delivers closing script on a timely basis.Initiates Customer Satisfaction Survey and identifies key call-outs for contact inquiry improvements.Be flexible to perform other HR Shared Services work as required from time to timeBachelor's Degree in HR or related fieldAt least 2 years relevant experience in Human Resources or equivalentWith excellent command of English, Thai and Vietnamese or With excellent command of English, Thai or Vietnamese and one or more of the languages in verbal and written: Chinese, Japanese, Korean and Cantonese (dialect) to support respective marketsPossess outstanding communication and customer service skillsExperience in a Call Center environmentTeam player, energetic, service-oriented and able to work in a dynamic and fast paced environmentAble to multi task, work well under pressure and deliver within tight timelineIdentify, analyze and solve issues in straightforward situationsBackground in HR Shared Services environment and SAP is an advantage Relocation AvailableNo Competitive Recruiting ProcessYes Is this a Liason Office LO RequisitionNo Expatriate TermsNo
